# First we should transfer all the letter in lowercase
train_data = train_raw
test_data = test_raw
train_data["lower"]=train_data.text.str.lower() #lowercase
train_data["lower"]=[str(data) for data in train_data.lower] #converting all to string
test_data["lower"]=test_data.text.str.lower() #lowercase
test_data["lower"]=[str(data) for data in test_data.lower] #converting all to string

# change all the char excludes numbers and alphabets to space
train_data["lower"]=train_data.lower.apply(lambda x: re.sub('[^A-Za-z0-9 ]+', ' ', x)) #regex

test_data["lower"]=test_data.lower.apply(lambda x: re.sub('[^A-Za-z0-9 ]+', ' ', x)) #regex

# Create a function to generate word cloud for each type
def generate_word_cloud(text, title, ax):
    wordcloud = WordCloud(
        max_font_size=100,
        max_words=100,
        background_color="black",
        scale=10,
        width=800,
        height=800
    ).generate(text)
    ax.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation="bilinear")
    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=16)
    ax.axis("off")

# Create figure and axes for the subplots
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(20, 20))

# Generate and plot word clouds for each type
types = ['Positive', 'Negative', 'Irrelevant', 'Neutral']

for i, sentiment_type in enumerate(types):
    word_cloud_text = ''.join(train_data[train_data["type"] == sentiment_type].lower)
    ax = axes[i//2, i%2]  # Position in subplot grid
    generate_word_cloud(word_cloud_text, sentiment_type, ax)

# Display the plots
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In[23]:
def show_details(dataset):
    missed_values = dataset.isnull().sum(axis = 0)
    missed_values_percent = (dataset.isnull().sum(axis = 0)) / len(dataset)
    duplicated_values = dataset.duplicated().sum(axis = 0)
    duplicated_values_percent = (dataset.duplicated().sum(axis = 0)) / len(dataset)
    info_frame = pd.DataFrame({'Missed_Values' : missed_values ,
                              'Missed_Values %' :missed_values_percent,
                              'Duplicated values' :duplicated_values,
                              'Duplicated values %':duplicated_values_percent})
    return info_frame.T
